-- Joe Johnson’s Basket Gives Nets 113-111 Overtime Defeat of Bucks
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-02-20T05:01:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-20/joe-johnson-s-basket-gives-nets-113-111-overtime-defeat-of-bucks.html
Joe Johnson  hit a basket with one
second left in overtime to give the Brooklyn Nets their third
straight win, a 113-111 victory against the Milwaukee Bucks in a
National Basketball Association game.  Johnson hit a 3-pointer with one second left in regulation
play last night to tie the game at 105-105 and force the
overtime.  The Nets (32-22) are two games behind the first-place New
York Knicks in the Eastern Conference’s five-team Atlantic
Conference. The Bucks (26-26) are third in the five-team Central
Division, 5 1/2 games behind the Indiana Pacers.  Johnson scored 24 points, while  Brook Lopez  and  Deron Williams  each added 19 for the Nets on their home court at
Barclays Center.  Brandon Jennings  scored 34 points,  Ersan Ilyasova  added 21
and  Monta Ellis  had 18 points for the Bucks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Nancy Kercheval  in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  